  "title": "(Senior) Data Scientist (AI)",
  "description": "<p><strong>about company </strong></p>\n<p>I am currently working with a telecommunications company </p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>Salary structure: Base + bonus. 5 days in office. 1-2 rounds of interview to offer stage.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>about job</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Partner with cross-departmental teams to uncover high-impact opportunities. Build AI/ML models</li>\n  <li>From concept to production, lead the development of models that assess payment behavior, creditworthiness, and support automated decision-making systems.</li>\n  <li>Design and execute structured experiments, A/B tests, and segmentation strategies to enhance marketing and lifecycle programs.</li>\n  <li>Lead initiatives that power smarter credit decisions, optimize credit limits, and minimize risk—using cutting-edge models and data-driven insights.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>skills and requirements</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Bachelor degree in computer science, or a related field</li>\n  <li>Min 3 years of relevant working experience.</li>\n  <li>Deep technical and data science expertise in ML Modelling, LLM, GenAI (e.g., GPT, LLaMA), linear regression, time series forecasting, segmentation</li>\n  <li>Skilled in SQL, Python, Spark, Hadoop/Hive, and Databricks and Power BI</li>\n  <li>Exposure to cloud platforms (e.g., Azure AWS, GCP) and ML lifecycle tools (e.g., MLflow, Airflow)</li>\n</ul>\n<p>To apply online please use the 'apply' function, alternatively you may contact Stella at 96554170 (EA: 94C3609 /R1875382)</p>",
